reviews.text: Coming to Maleny Dairies was the absolute highlight of my visit to Maleny. I love cows and it was amazing to cuddle and spend some time with the calves. They were so sweet and gentle and just beautiful creatures that made my heart smile.

This was the highlight of our 2 night stay in Maleny. We are travelling with our 2 kids (ages 10 & 12), and all had a wonderful time.

We were recommended to do the 10am farm & factory tour then take a tractor ride by a local friend. So glad we did - the tour was fun, interesting & delicious (free tasting of the Maleny Dairies products at the end of the tour!). Staff were all helpful, friendly and kind. Amenities were great. 

The tractor ride was also fun - a refreshing & relaxing tour through the stunning farm to see where the lucky cows live, and stopping to feed some more farm animals, including goats, sheep and EMUS! It was a hoot! We'd do it again for sure.

Just remember your hat & sunscreen - it was pretty hot the day we went, and we all got a little toasted.

This place is fantastic to gain knowledge about milk industry. Don't forget to book your dairy  tour ($11 per person). You can try to drink milk straight from the cow.  The tractor ride is good (if you want to experience tractor ride in farms and feed emus). 

They should add more items in the menu to cater more people.

We had a great time here.  Very good tour, great value for money.  Taste testing and excellent quality milk products available at discount prices. 
Kids had a fun time.  They're still talking about it and asking for Maleny Dairy milk.

A very late review as I went in July 2018 but I must write this as it was a fantastic experience. I forgot how much this cost but I do remember it was totally worth it. Sadly I've forgotten the names of the girls who gave the tour on this day but I do remember it was one of the girls first day giving the spoken tour and both of them gave a detailed insight into how the industry works etc. If the owner reads this I hope you pass this onto them! 

Of course their dairy products taste good too and is a fun way to remind yourself that the real stuff doesn't come from bottles. I highly recommend everyone to come here and support friendly local Aussie dairies farms!
Cannot wait for this weekend event

As many places as I've visited including Japan and other places, Kondalilla still presents to be my favourite daily adventure of all time! It's fantastic for a leisurely stroll or even an afternoon swim. If you're feeling really fit, take the great walk for the full 9kms or even longer tracks available! Beautiful lookouts and views really make for a picturesque experience!

Beautiful nature walk. Lots to see and do. The rock pool was extremely fun to take a dip in. So many different plants, trees and animals around. When you breath in that rainforest, you can smell a beautiful smell of nature and it makes you so calm and relaxed. Beautiful place to go and enjoy if your a nature lover like me!
Superb small national park in the Sunshine Coast hinterland. Excellent circuit trail to the falls lookout, bottom pool and return. Recommended.
Wondrous natural beauty with spectacular view points. Enjoyable bush walk and fabulous swimming hole. Picnic facilities.

A nice place to have a walk in the mountains.
The rock pool inside is awesome, good for swimming, just need to watch out that your feet can't reach the bottom of the pool.

Lovely view! The parking also offers multiple carparks so you, your friends and family can all park together. The map gives you a beautiful painting that offers you the names of mountains you can see.
Fabulous for a stop & look. Parking good for disability. No Cafe nor toilets.

Wonderful lookout + bins and table and map of glass house mountains. 
Make sure you go to the botanical gardens around the corner and pat a parrot.
Nice spot to view all the Glass House Mountains. There's a covered seating area for a cup of tea (bring your own) and a quaint painted guide to the objects in the view.
Lovely rest stop. Gorgeous scenery

Love this little slice of Italy right in the heart of Maleny township. When ever i visit i always make sure i get the Mediterranean chicken pizza takeaway with extra olives ....to die for. Next time I'll dine in the ambiance looks great.
Very happy with the pizzas and delivery. Pizzas.. We got 3 tonight and I got into each one.. Very tasty👍. To the one who delivered to Maleny Hills this evening.. You are fantastic 👍 thank you.

We got pizza and pasta takeaway. The food was ready when they said it would be. Good quality pizza, the pasta was delicious. Mmmmm ravioli and tortellini 👌 It's where its at.  Also, some winning garlic bread.

Overall nice staff, service and experience. Food as a little lacking though and I feel the other reviews don't really tell the story.

The cannelloni was quite bland and seemed as though it was not freshly made and likely just reheated from being made and stored earlier. Store bought frozen meal as opposed to a freshly made item like the name suggests.

The pizza was pretty standard but lacked when compared to other pizza places in the sense of the overall flavour, crust taste and texture.

Didn't warrent 4 or 5 stars in my opinion. The other 1 star review is a bit harsh also.
Meal was lovely. Great spot right on Obi Obi Creek to watch out for platypus. Great night enjoyed by all

If you haven't bought cheese from Colin James Fine Foods have you even been to Maleny? 
Insane, rotating range and staff who know their stuff
They have great food. They have a cheese section. They make their own gelato. I had a fig quiche and my husbane had the steak burger. Yum.

The cheese display in the front window is enough to stop most people ( and it does ) ....... then you walk inside amd realise its a seperate large walk in cheese wonderland fridge ! The lady serving was lovely and will be back more than once this next week to buy supplies. Other interesting food stuff available.
It's now called something else, Maleny Coop? Great cheese! Great ice-cream! Food is ok
Consistently great coffee and friendly personal serviice.
This a wonderful restaurant with loads of  character and an amazing variety of delicious meals on the menu. The service is first class and always friendly.

Honestly we were so incredibly disappointed with our experience here. The service was not great, we had to wait a really long time to just get menus. The food was very average and the bill was excessive for what we had. Won’t be back there again.

When I read previous reviews I think I must have gone to a different place.
Eclectic is a kind way of saying nothing works.  The steak covered (smothered) in a  lime? sauce was as bad as it sounds.  The homemade bread, which isn't, seems to have swirls of a Nuttela type ingredient which actually takes away from what is otherwise a wonderfully light bread.  I would like to say the food was interestingly different but really it was just disappointing.
Such a lovely place this is, the food is great, the wines are good and the host was very friendly. The whole family had a great experience.

Not a fan.
The gypsy wheel entree:
Pates were bland, loose and under seasoned. Bread was good but I doubt it was made in house. Too many flavours happening. Feta, olives, charcuterie, Mediterranean vegetables and pates do not match well with Indian chutneys.
The curry platter main was nice but fussy in presentation.
The ' Brazilian' brahman hump was the most disappointing dish. The meat fell apart, which I thought was a good sign but it was completely grey and tasteless, as was the liquid it was sitting in. The dish was accompanied by a bowl of rice; 3 slices each of tomato and cucumber; a green herb sauce; a small piece of frozen corn cob that was still cold and a bowl of black beans that were the tastiest and most Brazilian thing on the plate.
Our waiter was extremely friendly but, he forgot our order for a 2nd glass of wine with our main, which he was very apologetic of but then also neglected our request for a replacement bottle of table water.
The meals were served in an array of tiny dishes which serves to disguise the small portions and clutter the table. We left disappointed and still hungry for our $125 dinner. 
Such a shame because Leesa is so lovely and it's such a beautiful space and concept. My advice would be to simplify the very eclectic menu. Pick a few traditional "gypsy" style dishes and make them fantastic.
Best of luck

This is an amazing place for couples and family's Jen is absolutely beautiful 
Highly recommend mcartneys lake house
Beautiful place , quiet , lovely lake , the pool is so refreshing. Kitchen has everything you need. The lady is lovely. Will be back for sure
Wonderful, enjoyed our time. Beds lovely and comfortable, clean, opening onto beautiful surrounds. Highly recommend a visit, hoping to return. Thanks Jen
Beautiful location, great place for weddings.
Our stay was very comfortable.  The facilities were excellent and the house was spacious.  The surrounding were most beautiful.  We booked for one night but stayed for two.  Thank You Jennifer.

Delicious food. We enjoyed our visit and were very pleased with the dishes we had. Many choices on the menu with a Malaysian Chinese theme. Will definitely be coming back whenever we pass through. New owners too. Very polite and good service.
Beautiful fresh food and friendly service. Well worth the visit 😊
fantastic food ,great service its now our regular chinese we travel from Bribie Rd its a long way but with the new managers its worth it
Best Sweet and Sour Pork on the coast
Mild Curry Chicken is to die for...fried rice is amazing and they have such wonderful kind staff
Amazing food. Funny waiter. It was my birthday and they gave us the best table with a beautiful view, decorated the table for us and gave me a $35 voucher to return. A beautiful lunch
Wow! What an amazing experience. Absolutely perfect food, service and dining experience. Can't wait to come back!

This restaurant has a wonderful view of the hinterlands from Melany. It's a seafood restaurant in the mountains with an exceptional quality of food. Every meal on the table was a taste sensation. Visually also the meals were presented very well. Best baramundi my wife has ever had.even my chips were so good.
Great customer service and food! They asked when booking if it was a special occasion and on arrival the table had sparkles and ribbons and a gift certificate for $35 to return!
Been dining here for over 21 years. A fav. Always a great feed! So lucky to feast here and have a 10min drive home.

Extremely rude service. 
We only order drinks and got some really rude looks and attitude. 
When we pay she short changed us and insisted she gave us the full amount. Absolutely shocking service, will Never return. 
Totally ruin our nice day trip.

*The owner responded and totally twisted the story around. 
In fact I greeted you and asked if we could have a menu to look at, you were behind the bar doing stuff when we walked in if this refresh your memory... 

This is so shameful for a business, not only to twist the fact but to respond in such a disgusting manner so to “look good” to the public. 

Also I suggest You check your CCTV in regarding the change, I’m expecting an apology for that appalling attitude of yours and the fact that not only have you short changed us but also insulted my personality over your mistake. 
Absolutely disappointed and disgusted. 

I’ll make sure to share this experience with all my friends on social media so they don’t have to experience such nasty experience like I did.

On Saturday 16th March, 2019 my son and his wife had their wedding reception at The Orangery. The service was exceptional. The food was delicious and the owners were so friendly with nothing being too much trouble. This morning a lot of the guests returned to The Orangery for a scrumptious breakfast. Absolutely loved everything about the place, staff and view.

Had a lovely lunch here. The pork belly I am told (by my wife) was succulent and flavourful. Our 3 year old had the kids fish and chips and we have all pinched some off of his plate. My Texan chilli is hot (am happy about this) which is affording me time to write this. 
The fish and chips (adult) has almost disappeared for my father in law who has a rare allergy. The staff and owners have gone to the next level to ensure that this was prepared in isolation.
Finally the staff have been helpful and attentive.
Beautiful place and amazing food! They were nice enough to let me order from the breakfast menu even though it was lunch time! Definitely recommend.

Beautiful setting with magnificent views over the glasshouse mountains and to the coast. There is s choice of inside and outside/verandas seating. Delightfully decorated in cottage/vintage style. The burgers are tasty and the chips good. The service is friendly. Overall a lovely relaxing atmosphere. I was surprised with a beautiful little birthday cake when the staff discovered it was my birthday. Delighted to recommend this venue!
